news.title: Delhi civic body will use drones to verify property details in self-assessment forms
news.para: On a pilot basis, a survey has already been carried out in Mohan Cooperative Industrial Area on Mathura Road. The services of an organisation, which conducted a similar exercise in Lucknow and Varanasi, have been roped in.

news.title: Merger of fringe villages in Kolhapur civic body soon
news.para: Rajesh Kshirsagar, former Shiv Sena MLA who is now with chief minister Eknath Shinde camp, said, “The chief minister and deputy CM Devendra Fadnavis are in favour of the proposal. The government will try to ensure there is no opposition from the fringe villages. The merger will definitely happen this time.”

news.title: LIC Housing Finance & Bajaj Housing Finance hike lending rates by 0.50%
news.para: Bajaj Housing Finance hiked its rate by 0.50 per cent, and the lowest priced product for the salaried and professional applicants will be 7.70 per cent now, as per an official statement.

news.title: Jaipur development body issues rules for lease deeds for Gopalpura plots, shops
news.para: Under the plan, JDA will regularize around 700 plots and shops falling between Tonk road and Gujjar ki Thadi as there is a commercial land-use corridor of 72m on both sides of the roads as per the master plan.

news.title: Over 350 families don't want to give land for Noida airport Phase 2
news.para: The villagers have decided not to take the compensation that is being offered by the government and vowed to protest any attempt to displace them from their land.

news.title: Draft master plan for Thiruvananthapuram proposes a new airport
news.para: The plan, set to be presented in the corporation council, pitches the new airport near the outer ring road in city’s border and suggests land acquisition through land pooling.

news.title: Drone mapping of land completed in 41% villages of Rajasthan
news.para: The minister of state for panchayati raj Kapil Moreshwar Patil informed this in Lok Sabha while replying to an unstarred question on August 2. There are 11,304 gram panchayats in Rajasthan.

news.title: Over 15 dilapidated houses in each zone of Bhopal: BMC
news.para: According to the a BMC internal report, there are 15 to 20 buildings in each zone, deemed dilapidated. The most dilapidated buildings are in zone numbers 2, 3, 4 and 5, the report highlighted.

news.title: Defunct fire systems put Lucknow development body flats at risk
news.para: Many occupants of these flats complain that systems were faulty since the beginning and despite incidents of fire in the past the agency has not learnt its lesson.

news.title: Nagpur development body allots PMAY flats in quota to general category applicants
news.para: ​In another violation of state government norms, NMRDA has engaged a private bank to make the software and conduct the entire process of allotment of flat under PMAY, allegedly without mandatory tendering process.

news.title: Supertech twin towers: Worry & excitement in house, bubble-wrap for windows
news.para: The 48-year-old businesswoman and mother of two is hoping light will return to her third-floor flat in Aspire 1, whose facade almost grazes Apex - one of the two Supertech buildings that will be razed in another two weeks.

news.title: Homebuyers' body FPCE urges West Bengal CM to make RERA functional within one month
news.para: ​Forum For People's Collective Efforts (FPCE), an umbrella body of homebuyers that played an important role in enactment and implementation of RERA, expressed concern over real estate law RERA still being non-functional in West Bengal, leaving buyers at the mercy of builders.

news.title: Over 4,000 unauthorised constructions sealed in Chennai
news.para: According to a report shared in a recent meeting by the Works department of the corporation, 2,261 buildings among the 4,224 were issued lock and seal notices in the last fortnight, and 242 were given notices this fortnight.

news.title: Gurugram: Builders are ditching affordable housing projects
news.para: The developers said affordable housing projects were no longer viable for them because the government had locked the price at Rs 4,200 per sqft.

news.title: Blackstone in talks to buy Delhi's Select Citywalk Mall
news.para: The promoter of Select group has not added any mall to the portfolio in the 15 years of operation of Select Citywalk and with no plan for expansion, the owners want it to be part of REIT.
